 DAY III HIGHLIGHTS
 Kumble and Laxman stitched their seventh 50-plus stand in Tests  For the 15th consecutive Test, Pakistan failed to set up a century opening partnership. Their last 100-plus opening stand was between Salman Butt amp; Imran Farhat (109) versus India in Karachi, January 2006  When Laxman took the catch of Yasir Hameed at silly point, it was his 25th catch off Anil Kumbles bowling Rahul Dravid took his 50th catch off Kumble when he caught Butt. The Dravid-Kumble combination is the best non keeper-bowler wicket-taking combination for India. The record is held by the Sri Lankan pair of Mahela Jayawardene and Muttiah Muralidharan. The former has taken 63 catches off Murali  Butt scored his fifth half-century in Tests  his second against India  COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON 
